ition will be made hopefully the peaceful way," David said. \par \par \uc2  Haig and David stressed the importance of political stability in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development. \par \par \uc2  Haig said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth enjoyed by ASEAN countries over the past three decades was partly because of the region's political stability. \par \par \uc2  ASEAN groups Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, the Philippines, Brunei, Vietnam. Myanmar, Laos and Cambodia will join the group soon. \par \par \uc2  David said American investors generally praised Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms including the one allowing 100 percent foreign ownership. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia is a wonderful place for American investment," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the main problems American investors faced in Indonesia were a lack of people skilled with technology and the lack of transparency in financial \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  U.S. Department of Commerce figures show bilateral trade between the U.S. and Indonesia has grown more than 132 percent this decade with trade increasing from US$5.2 billion in 1990 to $12.2 billion last year. \par \par \uc2  U.S. exports to Indonesia have grown 109 percent from 1990 to $3.9 billion. During the same period U.S. imports from Indonesia jumped 146 percent to $8.2 billion. \par \par \uc2  Investment Coordinating Board data shows the U.S. is the third largest investor in Indonesia after Japan and Britain. \par \par \uc2  In 1995 U.S. investment in Indonesia was worth $2,7 billion. \par \par \uc2  The press conference also touched on U.S. congressman Patrick Kennedy's efforts to introduce a bill cutting off U.S. aid to Indonesia because of its human rights record in East Timor. \par \par \uc2  The state of Massachusetts also plans to bar companies that do business in Indonesia from doing business with the state. \par \par \uc2  Former U.S. Secretary of Treasury Lloyd Bentsen said he did not "think that such unilateral sanction or embargo are effective ... So. I'm very optimistic that this is not going to happen".. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Trade and Industry Tunky Ariwibowo said he had asked the American delegation to counter the moves by explaining to the American people that they benefited from American investment in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "It creates jobs for Americans. Also, the investors pay \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  to America," he said. (jsk/rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt3e009sr\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
