\par\par \b \uc2  STABILITY AND GROWTH VITAL TO ATTRACT FOREIGN FUNDS. \b0\par\par\uc2 578 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 April 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): In Indonesia and other emerging markets, political stability and rapid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would help woo global funds, chief financial market analyst at Lehman Brothers, Stephen D. Slifer said here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Slifer said that investors in the United States and other developed countries continued to look favorably on Southeast Asia due to a perceived political stability in the region. \par \par \uc2  "When you are going to invest in emerging countries, you first look at stability. As long as Southeast Asia can present a stable image to U.S. investors, it should continue to attract their funds," Slifer told journalists here. \par \par \uc2  Slifer was visiting Indonesia on tour to a number of key Asian markets. \par \par \uc2  He declined to comment on future political stability in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  But he stressed that leadership changes would determine future stability in some countries in the region. \par \par \uc2  He cited the current transition in China's political leadership as a case in point. \par \par \uc2  "It is important to see how smoothly that goes... Already there are political problems in the West of China. That obviously makes investors nervous," Slifer said. \par \par \uc2  "It is also true with Russia. What happens if (President) Yeltsin dies," he added. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia faces similar \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Speculation over succession - just who will follow President Soeharto - is common among foreign investors in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Slifer contended that with a well established political system, such as that in U.S., the transition of leadership should not be destabilizing. \par \par \uc2  Slifer advised that besides political stability, Southeast Asian nations should continue to pursue rapid, export-led \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in recipient markets of Southeast Asian exports, such as the U.S., would be mutually beneficial, he said. \par \par \uc2  "Hopefully, we can sustain a sound \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance and provide market access for everyone, rapid growth can be maintained and capital will continue to flow from the US and other developed countries," Slifer said. \par \par \uc2  Slifer predicted that the U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow by 3 percent this year, with inflation steady at 2.4 percent - lower than the market consensus of 3 percent. \par \par \uc2  Slifer cited a strong dollar, with reduced import costs, and a rapid fall in oil prices as contributing factors to lower inflation. \par \par \uc2  The analyst also challenged the belief that rapid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would encourage the U.S. Federal Reserve to further tighten \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Last month, the Fed raised \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  by a quarter-percentage point for the first time in more than two years. \par \par \uc2  Slifer claimed that currently high growth rates are an anomaly, having more to do with favorable weather than an overheating market. \par \par \uc2  Investors, nevertheless, remain nervous, believing that the current growth rates are cyclical, and thus expect the Fed to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Slifer, however, contended that this was not a typical business cycle as for the first time in over three decades, the U.S. government had implemented responsible \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies. \par \par \uc2  Thus, he said, the Fed may further increase \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but would do so only mildly, by .25 to .50 but not a whole 1 or more percent because this would trigger a recession. \par \par \uc2  Slifer predicted that with a good performance this year, the U.S. market would continue to attract funds from Japan, Europe and some emerging markets. \par \par \uc2  Deterred by the current banking crisis in Japan, and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  Europe with the impending monetary union, investors in the two would eventually turn to the U.S. market, Slifer said. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt4m00aw8\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
