\par\par \b \uc2  CLASS ACTION CASTS LIGHT ON JUDICIARY. \b0\par\par\uc2 608 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 May 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The lawsuit filed Thursday against the State Electricity Company (PLN) by the Indonesian Consumers Foundation (YLKI) for an eight-hour blackout throughout Java and Bali last month may have taken the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  by surprise, given its uncustomary nature. Kastorius Sinaga, a lecturer in social sciences at the University of Indonesia's postgraduate program, ponders this event. \par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The Sunday, April 13, 1997 blackout has ironically cast a light on our \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  legal system. It is the legal right of people to sue the government or state-managed \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  enterprises because of any neglect in giving the best service to the community. \par \par \uc2  This legal suit represented by the Jakarta Legal Aid Institute is called class action, a remote term in legal vocabulary. \par \par \uc2  It is likely that the community, the majority of whom are not law-conscious, will be confused, wondering whether the state-owned electricity company could be sued, especially since the blackout was not intended by PLN. \par \par \uc2  How is it possible that the Jakarta Legal Aid Institute, a small private NGO with insignificant power, could fight against giant PLN using an alien sounding term: class action. \par \par \uc2  It is therefore interesting to analyze the meaning behind this class action suit. \par \par \uc2  Originally, class action was a scientific term that political scientists used in referring to the existence of a collective action by a homogeneous community group. \par \par \uc2  Therefore, class action is often perceived as a labor strike or demonstration by a community group that is relatively homogeneous in terms of members' social status and type of work. \par \par \uc2  Society, however, indispensable of its background of professions, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  status and gender, is also entitled to launch a class action suit. It has the same status as consumers of products or services, provided by certain businesses and companies. \par \par \uc2  An important element in class action is the existence of a situation in which common interest and collective rights are proven to have been disturbed by a party that is obliged to protect them. \par \par \uc2  The form and method of organizing a class action suit vary, but it has the same platform, through representation by an institute fighting for the claims of a community group it represents. \par \par \uc2  The YLKI, in this respect, serves as trustee for all PLN consumers who have been prejudiced by the blackout by PLN. Therefore, the meaning behind the class action suit has expanded. \par \par \uc2  First, unlike before, our present and future legal system is no longer seen as a repressive device used by authority over the interests of society. \par \par \uc2  On the contrary, as the class action suit against PLN will show, the legal system should be able to protect the community from government's arbitrary behavior, especially in its coercive power as a political entity. \par \par \uc2  Second, the suit shows the important relevance of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  accountability in government bureaucracy, including in its institutions, especially considering that government institutions are monopolistic in the production of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  goods and services. \par \par \uc2  Entrepreneur spirit, professionalism and dedication to quality and consumer interest are key prerequisites of a market \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  system. These have not yet been displayed by government institutions in their capacity as principal players in our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system. \par \par \uc2  Third, the tradition of collective legal suits against \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  institutions through class action will gradually become institutionalized in our legal system. This will make the law a more interesting subject for legal practitioners. \par \par \uc2  Beyond the law, in the sense that it will become a reflection of an encounter between various interests and political forces, elements will be revealed which are seen as the main enemies of the law itself, that is: arrogance of power, arbitrariness and authoritarianism. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt5300bcr\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
