\par\par \b \uc2  Interest rate woes to cast another shadow on JSX. \b0\par\par\uc2 698 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding regional currencies and the rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Indonesia will continue to cast a shadow over the local stock market, analysts said. \par \par \uc2  Securities analysts predict that investors will be monitoring fluctuations in the regional currency following the last three weeks of turbulence. \par \par \uc2  John Rachmat, a senior analyst from Schroders Indonesia, told The Jakarta Post over the weekend: "I think concern over the regional currency will remain and investors would be very cautious to watch its direction. \par \par \uc2  "It seems that the market will remain in a downward trend this week," he said. \par \par \uc2  Southeast Asian currencies, including the rupiah, have been under severe attack since early July following the devaluation of the Thai baht and the Philippine peso. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said that the Thai government had yet to improve its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and next week's talks with the International Monetary Fund were expected to improve market sensitivity. Talks will center on the financial package to bail out the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The result of the talks between the Thai government and IMF will surely lead the market sentiment," one analyst said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , has increased the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  of its \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  certificate (SBIs) by several percentage points in the last three weeks to shore up the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The increase in the interest rate has dried up the liquidity in the banking system, causing a sharp increase in the overnight interbank rates. This incited a rise in deposit rates and caused a drop in trading on the Jakarta Stock Exchange. \par \par \uc2  The increase in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for SBIs, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's main instrument to tighten liquidity, had since been lowered by half a percentage point to 9.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  But the fall in share prices has continued despite the slight drop in SBI rates. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muha,mad assured the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  last week that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move to rise the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be temporary. He said the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be eased gradually depending on the market condition. \par \par \uc2  Other analysts attributed the share price drop not only to the interest rate fear but also to the change in the margin trading ruling. \par \par \uc2  He said that the ruling change had partly discouraged the trading activities because investors needed to meet more requirements to use the margin facilities from their brokers. \par \par \uc2  Tjandra Kartika, vice president of Mashil Jaya Securities, said that the dormant market was also caused by many investors cashing in their stocks to generate funds to buy rights to other companies. \par \par \uc2  Investors have to spend at least Rp 6.74 trillion to buy rights over the next four weeks, Tjandra said. \par \par \uc2  "The investors have to sell some the shares they hold now to generate funds for rights payments." \par \par \uc2  Besides that, most foreign fund managers were still on their summer holiday during August and September. \par \par \uc2  "It is a yearly cycle for foreign fund managers to pull back from the market for summer holidays," Tjandra said. \par \par \uc2  The introduction of margin finance regulations by the Capital Market Supervisory Agency (Bapepam) on the JSX, since August 1 this year, also cause a disruption, he said. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index fell by 6.4 percent last week or 46.336 points to 675.436 from 721.77. \par \par \uc2  DBS Securities said that the index was likely to touch the level of 650 this week. \par \par \uc2  The average daily turnover declined by 35 percent to 249.1 million shares changing hand last week in comparison to 379.1 million shares in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Average daily value also fell by 18 percent to Rp 520.2 billion (US$200.84 million) from the previous week's Rp 614.8 billion. \par \par \uc2  Most big-capitalized stocks lost ground last week with Telkom falling by Rp 125 to Rp 3,850, Indosat by Rp 625 to Rp 7,425, Cigarette maker HM Sampoerna by Rp 725 to Rp 8,325 and its competitor Gudang Garam by Rp 1,025 to Rp 8,850, Bank Negara Indonesia by Rp 50 to Rp 1,425 and Bank Internasional Indonesia by Rp 275 to Rp 1,575. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8b006o6\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
