\par\par \b \uc2  MARKET REPORT - Currency  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties \highlight\uc2  will shade JSX's trading. \b0\par\par\uc2 685 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the direction of the rupiah and other regional currencies will continue to shade trading activities on the local stock market this week, analysts and dealers said. \par \par \uc2  Securities analysts said that investors did not see any attractive incentives for them to enter the market given the current volatility of the rupiah, after the Thai baht and the Philippine peso were under attack in the last few weeks. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under severe attack for the past few weeks following the devaluation of the Thai baht and the Philippine peso early last month. Its value has declined by 20 percent this year, much of which took place in the past two weeks. \par \par \uc2  On Thursday alone, the rupiah lost 5 percent against the American greenback following the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move to abandon the currency's intervention band. On Friday, the currency suffered another 3 percent drop to close at Rp 2,880. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said that they are still confused about the direction of the currency in short-term but believed that it would stabilize in the next few weeks. \par \par \uc2  "Faced with such volatility, nobody dares to enter the market," one analyst said. \par \par \uc2  Tom Inglis, head of research at ING Barings Securities, said that \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the market would remain and rule over the fundamentals. \par \par \uc2  "I do not see any immediate rebound in the market and it might recover in the next three to four months," he said. \par \par \uc2  "It's just a blue week for most investors ... and nobody can do anything," he said. \par \par \uc2  American experts also have the same view, saying that the free-floating rupiah should rebound on the strength of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals in coming weeks, but volatility will still deter foreign investors until then. \par \par \uc2  "We may enter when we feel the likelihood of a stable exchange rate will increase," said Luis Luis, emerging market debt analyst at Scudder Stevens & Clark. "That will depend on getting more stability in Malaysia and Thailand." \par \par \uc2  Longer-term rupiah stabilization will most likely arrive via equity investment, a more liquid market in the country, Luis said. "As equity investors return to pick up bargains, we'll see the currency improve," he said. \par \par \uc2  Invesco Asset Management is much more skeptical. \par \par \uc2  It is bullish on Latin America and Eastern Europe but will tread lightly in Indonesia and other Southeast Asian countries amid regional currency \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Our strategy has been to overweight Latin America and Eastern Europe. We have increased our aggressive stance as the months progressed," Francesco Bertoni, head of the fund manager's emerging markets desk, told Reuters. \par \par \uc2  Pentasena Arthasentosa's Edwin Syahruzad said that macroeconomic fundamentals were no longer the case. \par \par \uc2  "It has turned into a microeconomic problem. How strong are the fundamentals of the company during the current volatile market?" he asked. \par \par \uc2  Christina Lim, of Harita Securities, said that most investors had to track sideways during this sluggish market and watch the direction of the currency in the coming weeks. \par \par \uc2  "We advise our clients to sell and watch closely on certain cheap big capitalized stocks in the coming weeks," she contended. \par \par \uc2  "Investors are rushing to stay away as soon as possible and sell at whatever price due to rupiah currency fall," she said. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite index fell by 8.54 percent, or 57.73 points, to close at 617.70 last week from 675.43 in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Average daily turnover rose 22 percent to 299 million shares last week compared to 249 million shares in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  However, the average daily value declined 9 percent to Rp 474 billion (US$175.55 million) last week, compared to Rp 520.2 billion in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Most blue chip stocks declined last week, with Bank Negara Indonesia falling by Rp 200 to Rp 1,200; HM Sampoerna by Rp 575 to Rp 7,675; PT Telkom by 225 to Rp 3,450; and the satellite company Indosat by Rp 75 to Rp 7,075 while Gudang Garam rose by Rp 675 to Rp 9,300. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8i0074o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
