\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah strengthens as BI raises  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 606 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah rose sharply yesterday to cross 2,900 level against the U.S. dollar after \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) raised one-week to three-month treasury rates, dealers said. \par \par \uc2  Spot rupiah was traded at over 3,000 level in morning trading. Soon after \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  raised treasury rates, the rupiah immediately soared to 2,845 and closed at 2,850/2,870. \par \par \uc2  "Overseas players are suddenly selling dollar to make profit, knowing the one-week to three-month rupiah is getting more expensive," one local foreign exchange bank dealer said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  raised one-week bilateral \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Certificates (SBIs) to 20 percent from 10.5 percent, two-weeks to 22 percent from 11 percent, one-month to 30 percent from 11.625 and three-months to 28 percent from 11.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  But it kept overnight SBIs at 15.0 percent, two-to-six day at 16.0 percent, six-month and one-year at 12.125 percent and 12.75 percent respectively. \par \par \uc2  "We expect the new rate increase to cause a more substantial contraction in the money supply so as to curb an abnormal depreciation of the rupiah," \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's Governor Soedradjad Djiwandono said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Target \par \par \uc2  But he said the monetary authorities did not set a specific target for the amount of rupiah to be soaked up by the higher treasury rate. \par \par \uc2  "It depends on the market," added Soedradjad after attending a meeting of the Monetary Board at the finance ministry. \par \par \uc2  Other board members - Finance Minister Mar'ie Muhammad, Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Saleh Afiff and Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono - also attended the meeting. \par \par \uc2  Afiff confirmed yesterday that state companies and banks had been asked to place part of their surplus funds in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's certificates in another effort to soak up liquidity in the market. \par \par \uc2  "This reminds me of a Sumarlin move, which shocked everyone in the banking industry," said Schroder Indonesia's senior analyst John Rachmat, referring to the tight money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  introduced by then Finance Minister J.B. Sumarlin in 1991. \par \par \uc2  "If the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to pursue this tight \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it could easily burn everyone in the market, especially small players," he said. \par \par \uc2  He contended that several small banks now faced serious liquidity problems. \par \par \uc2  And those banks could easily become default if the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  remained absent from the SPBU market, he warned. \par \par \uc2  Overnight rupiah on the interbank market reached 160 percent before easing to 40 percent at yesterday's close. \par \par \uc2  This could trigger bigger problems like those in Thailand, where several financial institutions collapsed, he warned. \par \par \uc2  "If that happened in Indonesia, foreign investors would certainly pull out their investment from this country," he warned. \par \par \uc2  He suggested the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  reenter the SPBU market, but with higher discount rates. \par \par \uc2  "It's better to reenter the market with higher rates than never," Rachmat said. \par \par \uc2  While rupiah was strengthening, share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange tumbled again yesterday, with the composite index dropping 1.5 percent to close 9.196 points lower at 590.530. \par \par \uc2  Stock brokers said state-owned PT Danareksa Securities and PT Bahana Securities conducted massive buying to stop the index from falling again. \par \par \uc2  But the two firms were exhausted because the market was still dominated by selling mood, they said. \par \par \uc2  Rachmat said the price of most stocks were lower than their book value given the current market condition. \par \par \uc2  He said most people could not foresee the direction of the market in the next few months given \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the currency market. (aly/rid) \par \par \uc2  Currency - Page 11 \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8k007al\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
