\par\par \b \uc2  No project rescheduling so far, say ministers. \b0\par\par\uc2 405 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government has not made any decision regarding the rescheduling of development projects despite President Soeharto's call last week to do so. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Saleh Afiff said here yesterday the government did not see the need to reschedule the projects because such measures would slow the country's development. \par \par \uc2  Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono echoed Afiff's statement, saying there was no need to postpone ongoing projects. \par \par \uc2  "So far we have not decided on rescheduling any of the projects," Moerdiono said after a ministerial meeting to discuss the currency situation. \par \par \uc2  Moerdiono, Afiff, Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Soedradjad Djiwandono, Minister of Industry and Trade Tunky Ariwibowo and several other officials have been holding a routine meeting since Monday to monitor the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  In view of the current currency \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , President Soeharto called on the government and businesses last week to review their investment projects and determine which should be given top priority and which should be postponed. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has dropped by over 25 percent since January. Much of the fall took place in the last few weeks following speculative attacks from foreign and local managers. The rupiah fell to a record low of over Rp 3,000 last week but it started to recover after \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  sharply raised its \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Afiff said the government had established a team to study some of the projects to be rescheduled. \par \par \uc2  The team comprised the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the National Development Planning Board, the finance ministry and the ministry of industry and trade, he told journalists following the meeting. \par \par \uc2  He did not say when the team would start working, but said some of the projects such as the disputed Timor "national car" project would not be rescheduled. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Minister Tunky urged businesses yesterday not to hastily raise their prices amid currency \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The currency situation is not stable, so I urge them not to raise their prices," he said. \par \par \uc2  Raising prices would only made it hard for businesses to sell, as the rupiah's liquidity had declined, he said. \par \par \uc2  The only way to cope with the crisis, he said, was by increasing their efficiency. \par \par \uc2  "Companies must make their best efforts to reduce production costs," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the ministry would continue monitoring the price and supply of production and would encourage more exports. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8n006sy\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
