\par\par \b \uc2  Shares prices up but rupiah falls. \b0\par\par\uc2 649 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah weakened further yesterday, dropping 100 points against the U.S. dollar amid eased liquidity, while local share prices continued to gain ground, analysts and dealers said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign exchange dealers said rupiah supply was adequate following the maturing of \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  papers totaling Rp 976 billion (US$348.5 million) yesterday and Rp 800 billion Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  "This forced the rupiah to weaken as people started buying dollars again. Confidence in the rupiah has not yet returned as the strengthening of the rupiah so far seems to be artificial, supported by high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," one local foreign exchange bank said. \par \par \uc2  Spot rupiah, which opened at 2,780/2,800 against the U.S. greenback, fell in a thin market to close at 2,875/2,890 on the back of eased liquidity, he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, share prices rose slightly with the Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index up 0.2 percent, or 1.224 points, to close at 555.462 yesterday, with a total turnover of 415.1 million shares changing hands at Rp 478.5 billion (US$170.7 million). \par \par \uc2  Morgan Greenfell Asia Indonesia's banking analyst Mirza Adityaswara said the market was waiting for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's next move following the slight easing of liquidity since Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  "I suspect this is just temporary and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  is testing the water," he said. \par \par \uc2  Head of research at ING Barings Securities, Tom Inglis, agreed and said investors were still cautious about entering the currency market due to continuing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Saleh Afiff reiterated yesterday the government would maintain the current tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  until the rupiah stabilized. \par \par \uc2  But foreign exchange dealers said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  was likely to gradually ease rupiah liquidity to prevent small banks from collapsing. \par \par \uc2  They said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  was helping small banks with short-term liquidity assistance. \par \par \uc2  "This helps the market breathe. The money is already there although it is still expensive," one foreign exchange dealer said. \par \par \uc2  He said several money brokers had been offering some banks huge sums of funds, ranging from Rp 250 billion to Rp 2 trillion. \par \par \uc2  "I don't know where they got such a huge fund. But the most important thing is that they help ease liquidity," the dealer said. \par \par \uc2  He said he fully supported the government's move to deal firmly with foreign banks operating in Indonesia which offered free-income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  overseas deposits to local investors. \par \par \uc2  "This time, I support the government because it (free-income-deposit offer) will destroy the market," he said. \par \par \uc2  The Ministry of Finance reaffirmed Tuesday that the interests received or accrued from deposits and savings held overseas through local banks or foreign banks operating here remain subject to 15 percent income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad said yesterday he had instructed the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office to investigate banks suspected of not collecting the 15 percent (final rate) income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the interest on deposits or savings they placed overseas. \par \par \uc2  "We already know that several banks have offered such an incentive (free-income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  overseas deposit)," Mar'ie told journalists after a meeting with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, I have asked the directorate general of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  to audit banks strongly suspected of waiving the 15 percent income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  they are legally bound to withhold on the interest on deposits or savings," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said currency trading was quiet yesterday, with overnight money stable at 20 percent. \par \par \uc2  They said some operators were taking profit in the swap market after premiums fell sharply. \par \par \uc2  Overnight swap dropped 2/3 points from 5/6. One-month swap edged slightly up at 75/95 from 70/80 in the morning, two to 110/125 from 90/110, three to 150/170 from 130/145 and six to 230/260 from 210/240 points. (aly/rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8s0072m\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
