\par\par \b \uc2  Businesses need clear direction. \b0\par\par\uc2 834 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 August 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Analysts and businesspeople are again urging the government to be firmly united in coping with the present financial crisis and to refrain from giving conflicting signals that could worsen the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  gripping businesses. \par \par \uc2  They said it has become imperative for the whole cabinet, not only the monetary authorities, to work together to cope with the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "We are still waiting for a clear-cut guideline from the government as to where we are being led. We have instead been given conflicting and, sometimes confusing, signals," said chairman of the Gemala Group, Sofyan Wanandi. \par \par \uc2  Sofyan said a clear direction was more crucial than ever because businesses and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  have yet to learn to live with the new market reality of floating rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "We have been living comfortably with a fairly stable rupiah for over 10 years. And suddenly we find ourselves in a volatile currency market," Sofyan told Indonesian and Australian businesspeople at a breakfast meeting yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Economist Anwar Nasution from the University of Indonesia's School of Economics also stressed the importance of consistent \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  signals to create sustainable macroeconomic management. \par \par \uc2  "The government may not realize it, but what we are facing now is a painful combination of currency and banking crisis," Anwar told the meeting, hosted by the Indonesia-Australia Business Council (IABC). \par \par \uc2  Analyst Sjahrir agreed, saying the "financial crisis we are encountering warrants overall \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform in the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2 , monetary and real sectors". \par \par \uc2  "The punitively high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  applied to stabilize the rupiah is doomed to fail if this move is not supported by reform measures to address the structural weakness of our real sector," Sjahrir said. \par \par \uc2  "And we are worried because what we have got so far from the government is conflicting signals from individual ministers," added Sjahrir. \par \par \uc2  "We are confused because one minister said this while another one stated different things," Anwar added. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir, chairman of the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Studies, Research and Development - the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry's (Kadin) think tank, briefed reporters yesterday on the impact of the currency crisis. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir shared Sofyan's view that the skyrocketing rise of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's certificate rate (similar to the U.S. Fed fund rate) to as high as 30 percent last week was a wrong price signal. \par \par \uc2  Damage \par \par \uc2  "This credit crunch is so punitive that it is now destroying the normal market mechanism. If these punitive high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are maintained much longer, they will eventually damage our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals," Sjahrir warned. \par \par \uc2  Both Sofyan and Sjahrir foresaw the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year to slow down to less than 5 percent from 7.98 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  "Growth at this level, though taken as fairly high in many other countries, would be painful for a large developing nation like Indonesia with a huge labor force," Sjahrir noted. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir also expressed concern over foreign debt burdens of the private sector which he estimated at more than $65 billion. \par \par \uc2  "About $34.3 billion of the total is to mature this year. More worrisome is that about 30 percent of these short-term borrowings have not been hedged against exchange rate fluctuations," he added. \par \par \uc2  "You can imagine the damage all this would do to the business sector, especially after the market value of the companies listed on the Jakarta Stock Exchange has declined by about 25 percent in just one month due to the impact of high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Sjahrir said. \par \par \uc2  Sofyan concurred that people now prefer to put money in bank deposits rather than in business ventures because sensible businesses cannot operate with funds that cost between 40 percent and 50 percent a year. \par \par \uc2  "When the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  offers 30 percent interest on one-month papers, commercial banks have to offer much higher rates to attract deposits and consequently lend at prohibited rates," Sofyan said. \par \par \uc2  He said the business community realized the money squeeze was simply a temporary measure to stop speculative attacks on the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "But we want to know when this crisis will end. How long will we suffer from this pain?" Sofyan asked. \par \par \uc2  Anwar and Sjahrir believe the credit crunch alone is not sufficient to lead the rupiah to a sustainable market rate. It should be coupled with concerted efforts to address structural weaknesses. \par \par \uc2  "The haphazard manner in which the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been tackling problem banks has not helped improve market sentiments on the rupiah," Anwar added. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir agreed that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, which are fairly sound, are not the most influential factors which form market expectations of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Other factors such as the lack of good governance have become the underlying concern among businesspeople, including currency traders," he said. \par \par \uc2  He is convinced the rupiah will eventually settle at a sustainable market rate under reasonable \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  if market distortions such as monopolies are removed from basic commodities trading. \par \par \uc2  "I hope the present situation will revive the momentum for long-delayed broader and deeper reform measures," Sjahrir said. (vin) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt8t00752\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
