\par\par \b \uc2  MARKET REPORT - Rupiah, shares weaken further. \b0\par\par\uc2 610 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 September 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Despite the restrictions on forward foreign exchange transactions, the rupiah weakened further against the U.S. dollar yesterday to cross the 3,000 level. \par \par \uc2  Local stock prices also fell by 1.4 percent, dealers and brokers said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign exchange dealers said the ceiling on forward selling to nonresident at US$5 million per customer could not salvage the rupiah as domestic appetite for the dollar remained high. \par \par \uc2  Spot rupiah, which opened at 3,010/3,030 yesterday, continued to weaken to close at 3,040/3,060, they said. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said trading in both spot and forward markets was very slow and the volume was very thin. Therefore rates were exaggerated, with quotes seen coming in $1 million or $2 million. \par \par \uc2  "The market is still very quiet. But when overseas players unloaded dollar, I saw domestic players quickly cover it. This situation will continue to shadow the rupiah," one local bank chief dealer said. \par \par \uc2  He noted that as long as \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  prevailed, people - especially wealthy locals - would continue to switch their rupiah investments, including in stocks, to dollars. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) fell 1.4 percent on continued \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over when the government would ease rupiah liquidity and cut down \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index closed down 6.955 points at 479.014, with total turnover of 205.2 million shares valued at Rp 283.020 billion (US$93 million). \par \par \uc2  Stock analysts attributed the continuing doldrums in the stock market to the rupiah volatility and regional stock market's bearish trend. \par \par \uc2  The president of a securities firm who declined to be named said the whole situation was already unpredictable and this further dampened the stock market. \par \par \uc2  "Everyone is selling a lot to get out of the market," she said. \par \par \uc2  She added that she had advised her clients to sideline until the market recovered. \par \par \uc2  "But we never know when the market will recover," she said, adding that the prices of blue chip stocks were already very cheap to buy. \par \par \uc2  Economist Sri Mulyani Indrawati said yesterday it was speculation and political issues, not \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, that mostly influenced the currency market and determined the fate of rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, the government should work harder to further improve the credibility of its \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making mechanism to prevent market hysteria," Sri said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign exchange dealers said that measures taken by the government to defend the currency indicated that it was actually reluctant to let the market decide the fair worth of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "The government floated the currency, but it did not let the market decide its worth. I don't know why the government is fighting all out to defend the currency while destroying the banking industry, stock markets and corporates," said one local dealer. \par \par \uc2  "In this situation, foreign banks prosper, while local banks suffer the most," he added. \par \par \uc2  He said many local banks had lost trading lines with foreign banks. Trading links had even been severed among some local banks. \par \par \uc2  In addition, large local depositors, especially individual depositors, had moved their funds to foreign banks as they trusted them more than local banks, he said. \par \par \uc2  The dealer said there was talk of Jakarta operators buying overseas dollar call options, suggesting an underlying tendency to be long on the dollar in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  environment. \par \par \uc2  Liquidity was slightly tighter than Monday, with overnight money last traded at around 35 percent to 40 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  maintained its rates for short-term bilateral certificates (SBIs) at a range of 15 percent to 30 percent and remained absent from the short-term securities market. (aly/rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt93007dn\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
