\par\par \b \uc2  Liquidity needs easing to stop crisis - Economists. \b0\par\par\uc2 622 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 September 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Economists have warned that the government should further ease the tight monetary measure to prevent a possible \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Mari E. Pangestu and Tubagus Feridhanusetyawan, both from the Centre for Strategic and International Studies, said yesterday the rupiah was on the way toward stabilization, thanks to the tight liquidity and the government's newest reform package which had given the right signal to the market. \par \par \uc2  "But it's time the government eased liquidity and lowered \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a healthy level even though it risks a continuing exchange rate fluctuation," Mari said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  She acknowledged that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , had initiated a reduction in banking \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  by cutting its short-term SBI papers. \par \par \uc2  But it would not be enough to stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities as the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  still kept rupiah liquidity tight, she said. \par \par \uc2  If \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  remained high and tight liquidity prevailed, the multiplier and domino effect would be large as defaults affect companies, suppliers and then banks, she warned. \par \par \uc2  Tubagus added the government should concentrate on containing inflation rates rather than exchange rates and let the market decide the value of rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Long-term, consistent and nonreactionary monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would also help reduce speculation on the currency," Tubagus said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under speculative attacks following de facto devaluations of Thai baht and the Philippines peso in early July. It has depreciated about 20 percent since then. \par \par \uc2  To contain speculative attacks, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  widened the now defunct intervention band from 8 percent to 12 percent. But the rupiah continued to weaken, forcing the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to intervene in the market. \par \par \uc2  After \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  about US$1.5 billion, and with the rupiah continuing to weaken, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  decided on Aug. 14 to float the currency. \par \par \uc2  The floating rupiah then overshot to over 3,000 against the U.S. dollar from 2,500 level. To help stabilize the currency, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  tightened rupiah liquidity by raising its short-term SBI rates and denying the money market securities (SBPUs). \par \par \uc2  Tubagus said current rupiah fluctuations were largely influenced by investors' expectations and perceptions on the currency and the country's overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation. \par \par \uc2  The government's newest reform package, announced Sept. 3, had helped calm the currency market and at some points regain investor confidence, he said. \par \par \uc2  "The sooner the government follows up the Sept. 3 reform package, the better. At least it will reduce current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Tubagus said. \par \par \uc2  He added that the government should fulfill its promises such as easing liquidity, reducing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , rescheduling or postponing large government projects and dealing with problem-ridden banks. \par \par \uc2  "The government should implement them all to maintain their credibility," he said. \par \par \uc2  Mari agreed and said the market was now waiting for the government's firm actions against problem-ridden banks. \par \par \uc2  But the government should, in the first place, make clear-cut guidelines on bank liquidations to prevent unnecessary panic among depositors. \par \par \uc2  Tubagus added the government needed to improve legal certainty, including on bank liquidation. \par \par \uc2  As the monetary tools were no longer effective in covering up problems in the real sector, Tubagus said, the government should launch another reform package to address the problems. \par \par \uc2  Transparent, consistent and accountable real sector \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would improve the country's efficiency and at the same time help improve people's confidence in the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Mari added the government's recent announcement on plans to scrap the National Logistics Agency's (Bulog) trading monopoly on several agriculture products, for instance, had given the right signals to the market. \par \par \uc2  "It signals the political will on part of the ruling power to end monopoly. The signal is more important for the market now," Mari said. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt9g000os\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
