\par\par \b \uc2  JSX's share prices to remain sluggish. \b0\par\par\uc2 565 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 September 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange are expected to remain sluggish this week because of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the currency market. \par \par \uc2  Securities analysts and brokers said over the weekend that most investors were reluctant to reenter the bourse without fresh incentives. \par \par \uc2  Mashil Jaya Securities vice president Tjandra Kartika said "I think most investors have lost confidence in the market and they will continue to track sideways until the market recovers". \par \par \uc2  Morgan Grenfell Asian Indonesia banking analyst Mirza Adityaswara said the government's decision last week to cut its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to reschedule several large projects was a good move. \par \par \uc2  "But it is not strong enough to stimulate trading activities," he said. \par \par \uc2  The government announced last week it would postpone projects worth Rp 42 trillion and review others worth Rp 63 trillion until the financial crisis hampering the country was over. \par \par \uc2  Fresh deregulation measures related to the elimination of market distortions and red tape was extremely important if the government wanted to improve investors' confidence, Mirza said. \par \par \uc2  "The reform packages launched by the government so far have not yet touched the basic needs like reducing monopolistic practices and distortions in the market," Mirza said. \par \par \uc2  Mirza said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's moves to lower rates on its short-term SBI paper over the last two weeks was encouraging. \par \par \uc2  But commercial banks deposit rates are still offering higher yields than stocks despite the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's rate cuts. \par \par \uc2  Mirza said he did not think the yields on short-term SBI papers would return to their early July levels when the rupiah started sliding. \par \par \uc2  Tjandra said high lending rates and the high rates on short-term SBI paper would translate into slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  "Theoretically such high lending rates will influence the whole \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and eventually our GNP will decline," he said. \par \par \uc2  "More deregulation measures in the real sector are needed to increase the country's competitiveness or else our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will stagnate," Tjandra said. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index closed the week 2.8 percent lower, or 15.55 points down at 531.079. \par \par \uc2  Average daily turnover fell almost 50 percent with 267.40 million shares changing hand last week compared to 537 million shares the week before. \par \par \uc2  Average daily value plunged 60 percent to Rp 325.35 billion (US$110.28 million) last week from 628.9 billion the week before. \par \par \uc2  "The market will not rebound in the short term and the trading activities will probably be thin," a sales director of a joint venture securities firm said. \par \par \uc2  "I think one-day trading will mark most of the market activities in the coming week," he said. \par \par \uc2  Both Tjandra and Mirza did not expect the composite index to return to its high 740 for quite some time. \par \par \uc2  They said the index could fall to less than 500 points. \par \par \uc2  Most blue chip stocks lost ground last week except Telkom which was unchanged at Rp 3,350 and Indosat which rose Rp 225 to Rp 7,725. \par \par \uc2  Cigarette maker Gudang Garam shed Rp 600 to Rp 8,500, its rival HM Sampoerna slid Rp 525 to Rp 6,825, Bank Internasional Indonesia fell Rp 25 to Rp 925, Astra International lost Rp 275 to Rp 3,425, BDNI dropped Rp 75 to Rp 675 and the state-owned BNI fell eased Rp 75 to Rp 925. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt9m000xu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
