\par\par \b \uc2  IMF urged to take active role in currency crisis. \b0\par\par\uc2 572 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 September 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  HONG KONG (JP): Indonesian Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad warned yesterday that the currency crisis sweeping Southeast Asia could lead to an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  In a speech to the annual meetings of the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) here, Mar'ie urged the fund to play an active role in preventing such crises. \par \par \uc2  "Although we are in favor of market mechanism, we are concerned about the excessive volatility of many currencies which undoubtedly creates \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the business community and could lead to an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  "In this regard, I urge the IMF to take an active role according to its mandate," he said. \par \par \uc2  Southeast Asian currencies have sharply fallen since Thailand effectively devalued the baht on July 2 due to its financial problems arising from a high current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and bad loans in the banking sector. \par \par \uc2  Among the hardest hit are the Philippine peso, the Malaysian ringgit and the Indonesian rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Since excessive volatility of currencies can hinder the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , we warmly welcome any regional or global initiative to stabilize currencies," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  Over the last two to three years, Mar'ie said, Southeast Asian economies were marked by high \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth with signs of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  overheating; enlarged current account deficits accompanied by inflationary pressures; growing short-term private borrowings and the construction of huge projects that were beyond the limits of their national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  capacity. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie said that countries in the region had recently addressed those problems through structural adjustments. \par \par \uc2  "As a result, there are positive indications that the currencies are in the process of arriving at a new equilibrium in the near future," he said. \par \par \uc2  In his speech, he outlined four measures Indonesia was taking to cope with the currency turmoil. \par \par \uc2  The measures included floating the rupiah in mid-August accompanied by tightening liquidity and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , trimming the state development \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 8.4 percent and abolishing \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and boosting exports while limiting imports, he said. \par \par \uc2  Despite belt-tightening measures, Mar'ie said Indonesia "reaffirms its commitment to discharge all of its financial obligations fully and timely". \par \par \uc2  The government will continue to take efforts to repay its foreign debt ahead of schedule using proceeds from the privatization of state-owned firms. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie said the government had also shelved US$35 billion worth of government and private state-related projects financed through borrowings and external credits. \par \par \uc2  "It is the government's opinion that a number of private megaprojects does not reflect the national priority, therefore they can be postponed," he said. \par \par \uc2  The objective of those measures, he said, was to lower the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was now at about 3.8 percent of gross domestic product to a maximum of 3.0 percent within the next two years. \par \par \uc2  In addition, the government should take action to strengthen the financial sector in cooperation with the World Bank and the IMF. \par \par \uc2  Following the market-friendly measures, the rupiah has now reached "a relatively stable exchange rate" ranging from 2,900 to 2,950 against the US dollar, depreciating by about 24 percent since January, he said. \par \par \uc2  "This relative stability is partly a result of the market's positive reaction toward the market-friendly measures taken by the government," he said. \par \par \uc2  "Fortunately, this result was achieved without sacrificing our foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he added. (vin/rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt9o0011v\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI Governor - high interest required in times of Rp/US$  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 626 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 September 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  BI(Bank of Indonesia) Governor, J. Soedradjad Djiwandono, said that high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  may have resulted in liquidity difficulties for the banking industry, but that the measures were needed, while the Indonesian rupiah value was still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to the BI Governor, in the long term, high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would bring structural difficulties to the banking system, as well as affecting capital market activities. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad spoke at a meeting organized by the Indonesian Business Association of Singapore, as reported by Dow Jones yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He said the high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were needed as a result of the free floating rupiah exchange rate and weakening in the rupiah against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad said the high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were necessary to control inflationary pressures which were exacerbated as a result of the rupiah depreciation. \par \par \uc2  In the middle of last August, BI increased the one month Bank of Indonesia Certificates(SBI) \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 30% and the three month certificates to 28%. The move was followed by the banking industry, which increased CD rates to as much as 40%, and credit rates to 50%. On the interbank money market, overnite interest soared as high as 250% for the smaller banks and 100% for the larger banks. \par \par \uc2  However, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has promised to lower the SBI rates each week, in stages. This week the one month SBI rate had dropped to 21%, with the three month certificates at 19%. \par \par \uc2  The governor warned that in the long term, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals would be a key factor in the rupiah value. \par \par \uc2  In mind of the fact that the market is very sensitive to the effect of the rupiah, he said, in the long term the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals would be the main factor affecting the rupiah movements. \par \par \uc2  For this reason, efforts to strengthen the Indonesian fundamentals would play a basic role. "A healthy banking sector will help the monetary authority to implement its policies more effectively." \par \par \uc2  Market conditions \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian rupiah exchange rate yesterday dropped about 2% to around Rp 3,127, triggered by US dollar purchases by companies needed to hedge their foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless, according to a market player, the high swap premium was still under control. "Normally when a rupiah fluctuation is occurring, it has a strong effect on the three month, and lower, swap premiums. But yesterday they were not affected." \par \par \uc2  The three month swap premium was offered at an average of 11.41%, down from 12% on Thursday. The one month swap premium was 11%, from a previous 12%. "While the overnite increased from 8% to 11%." \par \par \uc2  According to this market player, the attacks on the rupiah mainly occurred at mid day after the Friday prayers. Although there was an attack on the Rp/US$ rate, the interbank overnite interest rate tended to be normal. "The money market liquidity has righted itself. The overnite rate was only 15.5%, or 0.5% above the SBI overnite rate." \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  released Rp 1.533 trillion onto the money market in the form of redeemed SBI certificates. Still, at this time the absorption of banking industry funds through the SBI outside the auction system is calculated to be about Rp 5 trillion. \par \par \uc2  According to BI data, trade in the interbank money market was fairly tight yesterday. The overnite rate in the afternoon session averaged 30.22%, down 2.35% compared to 32.57% on Thursday. The volume of the session was Rp 1.98 trillion, while the morning session volume was Rp 4.89 trillion. \par \par \uc2  BI's open market operation showed a net contraction of Rp 5.5 billion as a result of a net contraction in the SBI of Rp 5.5 billion. (m2/ep). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dt9r00016\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  MARKET REPORT - Financial sector continues to drop. \b0\par\par\uc2 553 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 September 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The financial stocks were still un-recovered and tended to weaken in last week's trade. Although the macro condition of the Jakarta Stock Exchange(JSX) began to show improvement, it was unable to push the group of financial stocks to higher prices. The investors themselves were still cautious as they took position on the exchange following the still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  monetary situation in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The positive market sentiment toward several of the banking stocks was unable to bring up the sectoral index. It was reported that the enthusiasm of investors toward the banking stocks was a result of the improved Bank of Indonesia Certificates(SBI) \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  last week. \par \par \uc2  The monetary authority, on September 23, again lowered the SBI rates on all certificates from 1% to 2%. This move was considered sufficient to improve the liquidity of the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  banks. However, some investors were still reluctant to trade in the banking stocks because of BI(Bank of Indonesia)'s plan to liquidate unsound banks. \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless, the banking stocks last week contributed a gain of about 0.80% to investors. This contribution, though only in a small range, showed that the banking stocks have the potential to improve. The number of banking shares changing hands last week was 471.759 million shares, worth Rp 402.486 billion. On average the sectoral price/earning ratio(PER) for the banks at this time is 8.89 times. \par \par \uc2  The weakening in the financial sector was mainly the result of a drop in the prices of the insurance stocks. Last week the insurance group took a deep cut, of 11.15%. In addition to a minimum of rumors on the individual companies, the fall in price came as a result of the recent monetary fluctuation, which significantly hindered growth in the sector. \par \par \uc2  Very similar conditions were experienced by the finance institutions. The monetary crisis which has been eroding the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  lately has had a negative effect on the finance institutions. The finance companies were seen having difficulties covering their debt, particularly that in the form of dollars. The listed insurance companies last week only traded 55.155 million units, worth Rp 35.491 billion. Nevertheless, in terms of long term investment, the insurance stocks still have the potential to return high gains, particularly with a very low PER for the sector, of 7.36 times. \par \par \uc2  Overall, the trade in the financial shares last week was quiet and unstimulated. The minimum of positive information on the individual companies was also another reason for the low level of trade in the group. In addition, the still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  monetary situation, indicated by the continued weakening of the rupiah against the dollar, was the main factor in the fall in prices in the sector. Investors were holding back from trading. \par \par \uc2  In the coming week, the financial stocks are predicted to experience a meaningful change. The investors were seen waiting for continued action from the monetary authority to bring immediate stability to the rupiah exchange rate. Such a move by the BI(Bank of Indonesia) would encourage investors to again invest in the financial stocks. In addition, capitalists are also waiting for the publication of the first semester financial reports as an instrument for the purchase of stocks. \par \par \uc2  Sigma Research Institute. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dt9t0001a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
