\par\par \b \uc2  Property market severely hit by  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  crisis. \b0\par\par\uc2 581 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 October 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The excessive depreciation of the rupiah and high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  have made the local property market significantly vulnerable, an analyst and an industry executive said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  "The property market has been dealt a triple blow," property consultant PT Procon Indah, in cooperation with Jones Lang Wootton, said in a statement yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The first blow came from the sharp depreciation as foreign denominated debt affected many large developers, Bayu Utomo of Procon Indah said. \par \par \uc2  Developers with large foreign debt, but with revenue in rupiah, faced a 50 percent increase in principal and interest costs, he said. \par \par \uc2  The second blow, he said, was from high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ; they penalized rupiah-financed developers as banks automatically adjusted their lending rates, even to existing debtors. \par \par \uc2  And the third blow came from a weakening demand for property, Bayu said. \par \par \uc2  "Occupants and buyers, feeling the effect of higher inflation, higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and an erosion of wealth, have begun to curb their acquisition or expansion plans," he said. \par \par \uc2  He projected that the new property supply would decline in coming years because developers had delayed or canceled their projects altogether. \par \par \uc2  "This is a positive factor as it will potentially avoid what was to be a more serious oversupply problem due to current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Agusman Efendi, secretary-general of the Indonesian Association of Real Estate Developers (REI), said many property firms, especially small and medium-sized ones, had been forced to cease operations this month. \par \par \uc2  "And if the high (\b \highlight22\uc2 interest) rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  continue over the next two or three months, some property companies may collapse," Agusman told Reuters. \par \par \uc2  The association currently groups around 2,000 property companies, with 80 percent of them engaged in the construction of low-cost housing. \par \par \uc2  Agusman said most REI members depended on bank loans to finance property projects, particularly state-owned PT Bank Tabungan Negara (BTN) which specializes in financing low-cost housing projects. \par \par \uc2  Agusman said with most banks charging more than 35 percent for construction loans and 30 percent for mortgages, most property companies - especially small and medium-sized firms - would find it difficult to continue to develop. \par \par \uc2  He said the gloomy outlook was exacerbated by the rising cost of construction materials, particularly imported items paid for in U.S. dollars. \par \par \uc2  The value of the dollar has risen by more than 50 percent against the rupiah since the beginning of the year. \par \par \uc2  It stabilized at about Rp 3,550 to the U.S. dollar on Thursday after the government said it would seek assistance from the International Monetary Fund and other organizations to steady the currency and restore market confidence. \par \par \uc2  Agusman said some large publicly listed property companies were expected to weather the monetary crisis better than smaller ones because listed companies could generate cash from shareholders. \par \par \uc2  But property analysts in Jakarta said most investors were staying away from property stocks. \par \par \uc2  They also said some listed property companies faced serious cash problems from high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a large foreign currency exposure because of the dollar's gains. \par \par \uc2  An analyst with a foreign securities firm said property stocks on the Jakarta Stock Exchange were the hardest hit after banking stocks. Property share prices had fallen around 50 percent since early July. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said property companies had also been hit by the recent government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  prohibiting \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  banks from providing loans for land purchases. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  followed concerns that banks might suffer overexposure in the property sector. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtaa000xh\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  The government must be more open about the IMF negotiations. \b0\par\par\uc2 918 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 October 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The monetary authority has been asked to be more transparent in its handling of the problem banks as well as the type of aid to be offered by the IMF, in order to bring certainty to investments in the money and capital markets. \par \par \uc2  Spokesperson for the Presetya Mulya Group, Sofjan Wanandi, said the government must be firm in its handling of the problem banks. \par \par \uc2  "I figure they have a list [of the banks], and that the liquidation regulations have been drawn up. As well as the banks not to be handled right away. They should have the liquidation of the banks settled by the end of this month," he said to Bisnis recently. \par \par \uc2  President of Bank Arya, Safrullah Hadi Saleh, said the move to liquidate the banks should be taken only if it is absolutely necessary. The move could be taken if efforts to improve the banks have truly failed and an individual bank is deemed a threat to the domestic banking system. \par \par \uc2  "If a bank is liquidated, it will result in a lot of problems, and the settlement of the liquidation will go on for a long time, as it is at Bank Summa. Furthermore, it will affect the greater \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , who may have funds at the bank." \par \par \uc2  Guidance can be given to help the unsound banks, such as through the support of stockholders, reliable professionals and coordination with the Bank of Indonesia(BI) as the banking oversight and guidance body. \par \par \uc2  "The liquidation of a bank should only take place as far as the revocation of the bank's business permit, while the assets and obligations of the bank can be transferred to other sound banks through acquisition or merger." \par \par \uc2  Sofyan said efforts to settle the short term monetary difficulties should begin with the improvement of liquidity. "And the IMF aid should be oriented to the long term in order to improve credibility," he said. \par \par \uc2  At the same time, Didik J. Rachbini, Indef researcher, stressed that under the current circumstances of monetary crisis the government should not increase the price of fuel. "The important thing is not to increase the price of fuel, since such an increase could disturb the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  structure," he said yesterday in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  IMF package A market player said that firmness and transparency were not being neglected in the handling of the problem banks alone, but also in the aid package to be obtained from the IMF. \par \par \uc2  "The lack of transparency is effecting investors very strongly as they make their trading decisions. It is no wonder that even with the IMF on the scene, the rupiah is still decreasing in value. \par \par \uc2  The value of the Indonesian rupiah against the US dollar yesterday broke the Rp3,500 mark, to reach Rp 3,575, despite the fact that the Bank of Indonesia(BI) again intervened, by selling US dollars on the spot market for about Rp 3,495. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, BI data on the interbank money market situation showed liquidity still tight. The average overnite interest rate in the afternoon session was still high, at 29.42%, down slightly compared to the previous day's 30.29%. The volume of trade was Rp 3.061 trillion, and in the morning session the volume traded was Rp 4.691 trillion, with an average interest rate of 42.84%. \par \par \uc2  The Open Market Operation at BI resulted in a net contraction of Rp 688.67 billion thanks to the net contraction in the Bank of Indonesia Certificates(SBI) of Rp 688.67 billion. Today BI plans a daily auction of seven day SBI, targeting Rp 5 billion, to close on Friday (October 17). \par \par \uc2  Yesterday, trade on the JSX, according to a broker, was relatively quiet. The volume and value of trade was far below that of previous days. The broker said the investors were choosing to wait on the further developments of the continuing situation. \par \par \uc2  "There has been no clarification of the type of aid to be offered, which has resulted in continued selling," they said. The exchange, they said, has again lost the trade that had given it positive sentiment. \par \par \uc2  Better transparency \par \par \uc2  This broker believes that if certainty, in the form of the partnership with the IMF, which is what the investors are hoping for, is not clarified, the indexes may continue to slide. "The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the money market eventually affects the stock exchange. That is why the government must be more transparent in this matter." \par \par \uc2  A broker of the floor of the exchange said that investors are waiting for solid news on the form the IMF assistance is to take. However, this certainty has yet to appear, and in fact is as unclear as ever. For this reason, many investors are moving cautiously, and selling their stocks. In addition, the fall in the indexes is also being triggered by the weakening regional stock exchange conditions. \par \par \uc2  Herbert Liem, a senior Wall Street broker, who was born in Indonesia, stresses that in addition to the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the IMF aid, the domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also affecting the performance of the stock exchange and money market. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is predicted to go down until the completion of the General People's Consultative Council(a directly elected body that will select the President and Legislature of r the next five year period) session. I am convinced the investors will continue to wait and see until there is certainty, particularly in the matter of political stability. (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtag0001y\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
