\par\par \b \uc2  'Govt must be open on effects of crisis'. \b0\par\par\uc2 958 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 October 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government must be open about the effects of the currency crisis on Indonesia and what kind of international measures it seeks, as secrecy could lead to more speculation, the Institute for Development of Economics and Finance (Indef) has said. \par \par \uc2  Indef's chief analyst Didik J. Rachbini said yesterday the lack of transparency in information provoked more speculation in the currency market. \par \par \uc2  For example, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the financial aid package expected from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to help the government cope with the currency crisis had lowered \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  expectations about an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, he said. \par \par \uc2  "The market was initially optimistic about IMF's help when it was announced last week, until (Minister/State Secretary) Moerdiono said later that we were not getting money from them," he said. \par \par \uc2  "How can the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  be calm and rational about this if they have no idea what our position is?" he asked. \par \par \uc2  State secretary Moerdiono denied Tuesday that Indonesia was seeking financial aid from the IMF, but was merely seeking technical assistance. \par \par \uc2  IMF's deputy head Stanley Fischer said yesterday he did not know the amount of the bailout package for Indonesia, but said the package of measures could be in place in a couple of weeks. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has lost over 35 percent of its value against the U.S. dollar since speculative attacks hit the currency in early July. The government announced that it would either postpone or review US$35.6 billion worth of state-related projects to minimize the impact of the currency crisis, but analysts have said the measures are not enough. \par \par \uc2  Didik said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was ailing now and Moerdiono's statement only intensified the illness. The government must act as a social communicator to help ease the panic in the market, he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the newly appointed presidential economics advisor Widjojo Nitisastro could not fill this role as he was never very open with the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Veteran economist Widjojo was appointed by President Soeharto last week to help restore Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , on the same day the government announced it asked for IMF's help. \par \par \uc2  Didik said the press-shy Widjojo was a good technocrat 20 years ago when everything was kept in the dark by the government, but changes had forced the government to be more open. \par \par \uc2  "What we need is not only a technocrat, but also a 'techno-politician', because the current situation could lead to instability, not only economically but also politically," he said, adding that political action was needed to restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  trust. \par \par \uc2  President Soeharto and government officials needed to address the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the current situation and be more open about what the country was doing to cope with it, he said. \par \par \uc2  The President also needed to call on conglomerates to help the government cope with the turmoil and to communicate with the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  Indef's chairman Faisal Basri said the problem did not lie in the volatile market anymore but in how to restore the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's trust in the government. \par \par \uc2  "The confidential crisis has been building throughout the vulnerable history of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said, adding that the government had lost its credibility largely in 1986 when it last devalued the rupiah against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  "That afternoon we were told there would be no devaluation, but the rupiah was devalued the same night nonetheless," he said. \par \par \uc2  Indef's program director M. Nawir Messi said yesterday the institute predicted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would only be 6.4 percent this year, as a result of the crisis. \par \par \uc2  The drop was less than other predictions because Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had grown substantially by about 7 percent in the first half of this year, Nawir said. \par \par \uc2  He said he was optimistic that there would be a slight surplus in the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , because exports grew by 9.4 percent the first half of this year, while the growth of imports only amounted to 0.7 percent during the same period. \par \par \uc2  Based on this data, Nawir said the growth of exports would reach about 8 percent by the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  However, the ill effects of the currency crisis would continue into next year, when \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would decline further to 6 percent, he said. \par \par \uc2  "The country has suffered the effects of the crisis in the last four months of this year, but it will not be able to recover until the second half of next year," he said. \par \par \uc2  Explanations \par \par \uc2  In a related development, the United Development Party (PPP) and Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) factions at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  urged the government yesterday to give a comprehensive report on the rupiah at a plenary House session. \par \par \uc2  The factions' leaders, Hamzah Haz and Bachtiar Chamsyah, said they sent a letter to the House leadership asking for a plenary session to hear government explanations about the currency's turbulence. \par \par \uc2  "The government gave a statement to the House on Sept. 16 about the currency turmoil and what measures had and would be taken to cope with the problem," Hamzah was quoted by Antara as saying. \par \par \uc2  But additional explanations were warranted because the crisis seemed to be worse than earlier estimated, as could be seen from the government's request for IMF assistance, Hamzah said. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of the PDI faction Budi Hardjono concurred that the government should brief the House on the latest monetary situation. \par \par \uc2  His faction, Hamzah said, also insisted that whatever assistance was agreed upon between the government and the IMF during negotiations should be approved by the House before it was implemented. \par \par \uc2  "We need to remind the government that foreign loans for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector require House approval," Hardjono said. (das/vin) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtah0019t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
