\par\par \b \uc2  Be cool-headed and avoid stress - Expert. \b0\par\par\uc2 751 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 November 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Life today is a byword for stress, especially in a big city like Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Traffic jams, sweltering heat and the frantic pace of work are given problems. Now there is the additional trouble of the monetary crisis, hitting not only the capital but the whole nation. \par \par \uc2  Problems have avalanched following the sharp decline in the value of the rupiah in the past few months. Prices of goods have started to rise while salaries, if they have not been cut, remain the same. \par \par \uc2  That is if you are fortunate enough to have a job. Many business owners, complaining of a slump in orders, have laid off employees. \par \par \uc2  Things are getting a little bit better now, thanks to the government's landmark efforts to intervene, particularly with the closure of 16 "delinquent" banks. \par \par \uc2  Yet, stress is still here. Many are gripped by fears over an inevitable recession. \par \par \uc2  In their frustration, they grumble, complain and cry. \par \par \uc2  It's acceptable to do this as long as you know when to stop and start picking up the pieces, according to socio-psychologist Sartono Mukadis. \par \par \uc2  "My philosophy is that if someone dies, and everyone cries, who will bury the dead?" Sartono said. \par \par \uc2  "Crying is okay, but don't cry all the time. Be cool-headed. Start thinking and find the solution. Ask yourself, what's the point of crying, being upset, angry, fighting, or even taking your case to court. That will only bring disadvantages to us." \par \par \uc2  Some of us have the burden of redundancy hanging over our heads. Sartono says that if the dreaded pink slip does land on your desk, swallow some pride. \par \par \uc2  "If you are laid off, take the severance pay and then think about what to do. Is there any possibility that you can get a new job? \par \par \uc2  If not, and you are a man whose wife does not work, is it possible for her to become the breadwinner? Or is it possible to run your own business? Gather all possibilities and analyze. Learn your strength and weaknesses, and see the opportunities and the threats." \par \par \uc2  Sartono refutes the notion that people are stuck in fixed career paths and cannot turn their hand to other skills. \par \par \uc2  The source of the stress is not the layoff but the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that lies ahead, Sartono said. \par \par \uc2  "It (the layoff) is only a trigger factor. It's the fear that we won't be able to solve the problems that leads to the stress." \par \par \uc2  He said those who believed there were answers to the problem would be composed. \par \par \uc2  "It's like in the traffic jams. If you know that there are policemen to clear the traffic, or that the traffic jams will be over, then you won't get stressed. \par \par \uc2  "In this situation (the monetary crisis), if you know that there are ways to solve the problem, things will be less stressful." \par \par \uc2  He underlined the need for keeping a level head. \par \par \uc2  "Don't be overcome by emotion. Think rationally. \par \par \uc2  "The government is working hard to handle the situation. This takes time, but if you don't want to be stressed, you should trust them." \par \par \uc2  He said the monetary situation would get worse if there were uncontrollable variables, such as groups fomenting unrest by playing on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's fears. \par \par \uc2  "Fortunately, so far we don't see this variable occurring. So, please, be calm." \par \par \uc2  He recommended that people steel themselves to face reality and use reason to deal with the situation. \par \par \uc2  "Our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth has been predicted to decrease from about 7 percent to 3 or 4 percent in the coming years. So, don't ever count the money in other people's pockets." \par \par \uc2  Some may turn to friends and relatives for help, but Sartono cautioned that real solutions lie within ourselves. \par \par \uc2  "It's you who has to make a decision and act. Try to do something; however small it is, it might help. And remember one thing, don't become a merchant of sadness, asking others to take pity on you and lend a hand. That won't help. \par \par \uc2  The time to act is now. \par \par \uc2  "I know it is not easy. but if we don't start from now, things will be too late. Stop mourning and start working. \par \par \uc2  "If you are not able to cope with emotion and are carried away with the stress, you will plunge into a bottomless well." \par \par \uc2  Dwelling endlessly on the troubles, Sartono warned, could "make you crazy". (sim) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtbg002an\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Salim not to invest in any more banks. \b0\par\par\uc2 699 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 November 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Salim Group does not plan to invest further in the banking sector in the near future, following a purchase of a 19% share in Bank Danamon, said the President of the Board of Directors. \par \par \uc2  "We are satisfied with our investment in the banking sector, and for the near future we will not make further investments in the sector," said Anthony Salim, President and CEO of Salim Group, in Jakarta yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He acknowledged that there were many rumors circulating that Salim Group through Bank Central Asia(BCA) had invested funds in several more banks, or even had bought shares in them. \par \par \uc2  Salim Group, he said, only bought shares in Bank Danamon to form a strategic alliance with another bank, though the cooperation between them will be limited. \par \par \uc2  The Salim Group Chief explained that to date his organization had only formed partnerships with Bank Utama and Bank Multicor. "We are also providing technical assistance to Bank Yama and do not plan to increase our ownership in that bank at this time." \par \par \uc2  Anthony says BCA has been providing technical assistance to Bank Yama for the last six months. \par \par \uc2  Previously, the Managing Director at BCA, Abdullah Ali, said that BCA was providing management assistance to Bank Yama in order to restore soundness to the problem bank and to strengthen the national banking system. (Bisnis, May 19) \par \par \uc2  On that occasion, Ali did not comment on rumors that BCA was also providing assistance to Bank Utama. \par \par \uc2  Anthony acknowledged that BCA was working in cooperation with Bank Utama. \par \par \uc2  Rumors denied \par \par \uc2  At a separate location, Usman Atmadja, owner of Bank Danamon, denied various rumors surrounding Bank Danamon, that said in the end that part of its shares had to be surrendered to Salim Group under duress. \par \par \uc2  Several rumors came to the surface, including the transfer of Bank Danamon shares as a result of liquidity difficulties during the monetary crisis. There was even a rush on the bank. \par \par \uc2  Bank Danamon is also reported to have been in competition with BCA, with the two banks spreading unfavorable rumors about each other, which in the end resulted in a rush on both banks. \par \par \uc2  In another rumor, Bank Danamon decides that the future of the banking industry is increasingly \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and is selling its shares off little by little. Still another rumor said that Bank Danamon had significant foreign exchange losses after being too expansive in the dealing room. \par \par \uc2  "All those rumors are not true," said Usman to the press. \par \par \uc2  He says the object of his sale of a 19% share in Bank Danamon to the Salim Group was simply to increase synergy between the two. \par \par \uc2  The reason he gave was predicted slow \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the future, triggered by a poor \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation. For this reason, he said, Bank Danamon had intentionally formed a strategic alliance with Salim in order to bring mutual strength in the face of a difficult situation. \par \par \uc2  "That is the main reason, and there is no other secret reason," he said. \par \par \uc2  Another object of the sale, said Usman, was to use the proceeds from the sale to deposit into the bank. The funds are also earmarked to add to the reserve capital at Bank Danamon, if needed. \par \par \uc2  Keeping in mind that Bank Danamon is growing steadily, he said, the bank will require big capital in order to support the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of scale of its business. "Everyone knows Salim Group is a successful business group." \par \par \uc2  According to Usman, Salim Group is not only a success in industry, trade and consumer goods, but also in the banking sector. This success is not only experienced domestically, but also in the international arena. "It is hoped that this alliance will have a positive effect on Bank Danamon." \par \par \uc2  Anthony Salim explained that his choice to invest in Bank Danamon rested in the soundness of the bank. The performance of Bank Danamon has shown good development all year, good growth. \par \par \uc2  Usman added that Bank Danamon was an increasingly big \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  bank. "Wherever you go large banks are not controlled by just one or two individuals. But more than that, this will allow healthy growth at the bank." (m2/09/rr). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtbi0006u\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Lowered  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2  have yet to stimulate market. \b0\par\par\uc2 411 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 November 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The agreement between the private (Perbanas) and government (Himbara) owned banks to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 1-2% and credit rates from 30% to 25%, have not been able to stimulate the capital market. Foreign investors were seen holding back even more and waiting for continuing monetary developments. \par \par \uc2  The total Indonesian foreign debt by September of this year, was said by Mar'ie Muhammad to be about US$ 117.3 billion. This level of debt has investors pessimistic that Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will recover quickly. Particularly with a high rate of inflation and a weakening Indonesian rupiah exchange rate, the confidence of the investors is disappearing. \par \par \uc2  The highly weakened macroeconomic condition is reinforcing the doubts of the investors in the rapid recovery of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . That is why the lowered \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are being met with negative sentiment. \par \par \uc2  This has made the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) Composite Price Index, which had just been showing improvement, drop again, by 5.329 points (1.21%) to 434.209. As a result of this, Bisnis Indonesia's index of the top 40 choice stocks on the Jakarta exchange, the BI-40 Index, fell back 1.357 points (1.38%), from 98.438 to 97.081. \par \par \uc2  The increasingly \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  market situation resulting from the monetary crisis brought the confidence of investors way down. Add to this the financial crisis now occurring at the companies, which is putting the performance of the companies below 1997 predictions. This made the investors uninterested in returning to the exchange. \par \par \uc2  The market, which has an integral psychological factor, is having difficulty restoring a measure of confidence to the investors. Any and all of the government policies are seen unable to bring very meaningful results. \par \par \uc2  In yesterday's trade, the exchange activities were still dominated by selling action. This could be seen in the drop in price in the majority of the major stocks, which were traded at a large volume. Of the BI-40 Index stocks, 16 showed corrected prices, four stocks showed gains, and the remainder were stagnant. \par \par \uc2  Ramayana Lestari Sentosa stock had the greatest losses, by 11 points, from Rp 5,275 to Rp 5,000. This was followed by Gudang Garam, corrected nine points, to Rp 8,475, at a volume of 856,000 shares, Indah Kiat P&P, down three points to Rp 975, at a volume of 4.843 million shares. (*). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtbj00071\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
