\par\par \b \uc2  Confidence crisis not yet over despite aid - Expert. \b0\par\par\uc2 667 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 November 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The turmoil that continues to hit the rupiah and the local stock market indicates that confidence has yet to return to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  despite an International Monetary Fund bailout, an economist has said. \par \par \uc2  The executive director of the Center for Strategic and International Studies, Mari Elka Pangestu, said yesterday the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  had slowed down efforts to strengthen both the rupiah and the stock market. \par \par \uc2  "We are experiencing the contagious effect of the region's jitters," she said. \par \par \uc2  She said in Japan, the market was nervous about the possible closure of the country's securities companies. \par \par \uc2  People wondered whether China would adjust its currency to compete with the lowered value of other currencies in the region, and whether the currencies of India and Brazil would be hit by the domino effect of the downfall of Southeast Asian currencies, she said. \par \par \uc2  Speculative attacks, triggered by the devaluation of the Thai baht, had led to about a 35 percent drop of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  The currency crisis also hit other countries in the region, dragging down the values of the Malaysian ringgit, the Filipino peso and even the usually robust Singaporean dollar. \par \par \uc2  Last week, the Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index hit a four-year low, breaking through the psychological 400-point barrier, upon the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's announcement of the country's foreign loans. The index has since sluggishly picked up. \par \par \uc2  Mari said internal factors also greatly affected the low confidence in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Foreign and local investors were still waiting for the full implementation of the government reform package established early this month as a concession for the IMF-led financial package. \par \par \uc2  The market was also fazed by the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the private sector's short-term loans that were going to mature soon, she said. \par \par \uc2  The private sector was wondering whether the government would help bail out the companies with the maturing loans, and whether the loans would create more problems, she said. \par \par \uc2  Both the government and the private sector must take an approach to reduce this \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , she said. \par \par \uc2  Mari said the IMF package, containing standby loans of about $23 billion, did not necessarily help in solving the problems. \par \par \uc2  "The IMF cannot 100 percent guarantee that we will get out of this shackle. We will have to wait until the implementation of the reforms takes effect on our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said. \par \par \uc2  Unless the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was reduced, the country would not be able to improve its weaknesses and avoid similar crises in the future, she said. \par \par \uc2  Mari predicted the crisis would likely be over after several more months. \par \par \uc2  However, the crisis would be followed by an after-shock in the forms of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession and stagflation as the result of the financial turmoil in the next one to three years, she said. \par \par \uc2  Japan still suffered from lower growth and a recession since the early 1990s when its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  bubbled, while Mexico has finally begun to recover after two years, she said. \par \par \uc2  In an optimistic scenario, Mari said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  might recover by the end of next year or the beginning of 1999, if supported by the return of foreign investors and good governmental measures. \par \par \uc2  After the recovery, the government must set a mid-term and long-term strategy to prevent similar crises from occurring again. \par \par \uc2  This would show people and investors that Indonesia was serious about its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  vision, she said. \par \par \uc2  The mid-term reforms would focus on how to boost non-oil and gas exports, and improve human resources and infrastructure, she added. \par \par \uc2  Mari said the crisis was also a wake up call for large companies and conglomerates to be less diverse in the future. \par \par \uc2  Many companies expanded too rapidly and took out too many loans, resulting in a desperate situation now. \par \par \uc2  These companies must instead focus on their core business to increase their exports, she said. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtbq002dr\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Manufacturing stocks last week. \b0\par\par\uc2 426 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 November 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The increasingly \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  macro conditions of the Jakarta Stock Exchange(JSX) was not profitable to any investment on the JSX. This was also true for the manufacturing stocks, which had their prices cut deeply in last week's trade. On average, these stocks corrected about 13.73%. The sectoral index corrected by 10% in last week's trade, from 67.49 to 60.33. \par \par \uc2  The activity of investors on the exchange was unstimulated and characterized by \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the continuing worsening in the JSX. The monetary crisis lashing the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the last three months has made an increasing large gash in the capitalists' \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The price of stocks has fallen left and right, with the increasingly hard to predict movements of the JSX Composite Price Index, despite good corporate action on the part of some of the manufacturing emitters. \par \par \uc2  PT Indocement Tunggal Prakarsa, for example, has just received a 15 billion yen loan, equivalent to Rp 400 billion, from five Japanese banks. The funds from the loan will be used to finance expansion of its cement production facilities. This is the first such loan to any private Indonesian company. Yet the ability of this company was received coldly by the investors. In fact the price of the largest cement producer in Indonesia dropped 4.41%. \par \par \uc2  The biggest corrections in price occurred at Gajah Tunggal, by 39%. This was followed by Bakrie & Brothers, down 35%, Modern Photo down 25%and so forth. Overall, the number of manufacturing shares changing hands last week was 132.063 million shares worth Rp 187.426 billion. The average sectoral price/earning ratio(PER) was 7.76 times. \par \par \uc2  It must be acknowledged that the weakening in the manufacturing stocks recently was in line with weak macrodevelopments on the JSX. This weakening in the stock exchange began with the monetary crisis, which put pressure on the rupiah exchange value on the money market. The beating of the monetary storm, accompanied by the tight money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  hit the business community hard, including the manufacturers. \par \par \uc2  Many manufacturing companies have had funding difficulties due to soaring bank \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Unfortunately smooth running production depends highly on the availability of sufficient raw materials, and this has made it difficult for the manufacturing companies, particularly those which must import raw materials. \par \par \uc2  In general, trade in the manufacturing stocks is predicted to continue to show losses this week, and this is in line with the macroconditions on the JSX, which have yet to show recovery. \par \par \uc2  Sigma Research Inc. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtbq0008a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
