\par\par \b \uc2  Selecting the right technology. \b0\par\par\uc2  By Markus Krisetya. \par \uc2 1,231 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 December 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  SALATIGA (JP): In the current foreseeable horizon of development possibilities, technology appears to be one of the most important factors of production. If properly selected and implemented, technology can have positive and lasting effects for a country's overall development agenda. \par \par \uc2  Many developing countries have championed this cause and have rushed onto the technology-intensive development bandwagon under the banners of highly optimistic and futuristic visionaries. \par \par \uc2  The results have often fallen short of the rhetoric that underlies these movements. What then defines the critical success factors of these technology-intensive development strategies? \par \par \uc2  It must be recognized that the field of development studies and development planning takes place in a very \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  environment. While there are concrete goals, there are no definitive plans that apply to all situations. \par \par \uc2  On one side, theorists struggle over the process of conceptualizing different methodologies that have unproven outcomes and on the other side practitioners experiment with real-life dynamic situations without adequate tools. \par \par \uc2  One theory that works in one country may not work in another. Plans that are effective in one area may have tenuous effects in a different region. This dilemma points out the necessity to make development planning a process that is highly contextual. \par \par \uc2  Theories and concepts that claim to address all the issues and have the ability to outline the future should be approached with great caution and suspicion. \par \par \uc2  Kenichi Ohmae's flying geese pattern has captured the imagination of many people. His idea is that countries of the Pacific Rim (Japan, the NIC's and most of the ASEAN countries) are flying in the triangular formation of geese in their differing levels of development. \par \par \uc2  Geese in the back can ultimately fly ahead of the formation because the leader has set the direction. The reality as we see it today is that some geese in the back are getting a little lost in flight. \par \par \uc2  The same degree of prudence should be applied to the theory of Kondratiev Waves. This theory claims to have plotted out the course of history into predictable periods of recession and expansion. \par \par \uc2  These waves or cycles include elements of the rise and fall of hegemonic powers, demographic differences as well as predominant technologies that shape a particular era. The seemingly lucid nature of the future in this theory gives the impression that if certain countries accurately time their strategy at the beginning of a particular period of expansion; they can ride out a bountiful wave of prosperity. \par \par \uc2  But this theory is only as good as one's hindsight. The waves that have been plotted are part of history. None of the proponents of this theory can agree where we are exactly in the next Kondratiev Wave of the future. \par \par \uc2  So how does a country truly benefit from the use of technology in development? First of all, technology must be understood as something that can not be transported miraculously from one country to another with the expectation that the new user can reap the same benefits. \par \par \uc2  Technology, whether in the form of capital goods or in the form of knowledge, does not exist in a vacuum. Inherent in technology is an entire set of norms, values and laws that make the technology work. \par \par \uc2  Therefore in a sense technology introduces social change as it challenges preexisting social structures and creates new ones. This implies that without the necessary social structures that adapt to these requirements, technology will not be adapted. \par \par \uc2  These prerequisites extend from certain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  infrastructures (capital, policies and markets) and certain social infrastructures (skills embodied in labor and organizations) which provide the necessary environment that is conducive for technology to take root and have a lasting impact. None of these requirements can be created instantaneously. They are part of a long-term investment. \par \par \uc2  The second important aspect of the nature of technology is a consequence of the above requirements. Because the infrastructures are inherently long term in nature, it follows that technology possesses this same characteristic. Actual benefits of technology can not be expected in a short period of time nor can we expect it have a lasting impact if it does. \par \par \uc2  With these characteristics in mind, it becomes clear that for a country to embark on technology-intensive development strategies the country is required to seriously look at their immediate strengths and weaknesses. \par \par \uc2  A realistic perspective must replace the overly optimistic and futuristic rhetoric. Countries must recognize and address \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social infrastructures to enable them to choose appropriate technology applications in their development strategy. \par \par \uc2  One particular development theory provides a specific framework that is more appropriate than others when it comes to applying technology to development. \par \par \uc2  This theory is called the Regulationist theory. There are two components to this theory. The first, called a mode of \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is the component that explains the social relationships and institutions in society that define its behavior and activity. \par \par \uc2  It defines the rules of the game. For instance, in the labor-wage relationship the mode of \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  defines the organization of labor, the agreed upon length and intensity of the workday, conditions of employment and the distribution of direct and indirect wages. \par \par \uc2  The second part is called a regime of accumulation. Briefly this component describes how the social relationships and institutions of the mode of \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  give rise to the way in which distribution, exchange and consumption in a society works. \par \par \uc2  To expand a certain industry requires the expansion of industries supplying intermediate inputs to the production process as well as expansion of the demand for the output. The two components are in no way static. They can evolve and adapt but they are always inextricably linked with each other. \par \par \uc2  Every development theory has its weaknesses. But what makes the Regulationist theory appealing is that in reality it is a framework that allows for the local and historical context to be incorporated into its specific applications. \par \par \uc2  It outlines the elements in the background of the development process. It allows a more objective view of the relative success and failures from the perspective of inherent characteristics specific to each country in a period of time. As a result with respect to the nature of technology, the Regulationist approach becomes a very instructive way of planning for technology-intensive development strategies. \par \par \uc2  The relative successes and failures of technology-intensive development strategies become a complex interaction of the elements outlined above. \par \par \uc2  Failures are often a result of the lack of attention to one or more particular aspects of the equation. It could be a case of too little capital, a failure in the mode of \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the form of wages, the lack of an adequate pool of appropriate skills or lack of demand in the market. \par \par \uc2  Because of the linkages and tight relationship of the elements, a failure in one aspect can cause the collapse of the entire strategy. \par \par \uc2  However, understood in the context of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that faces development planners, there is room for failure. \par \par \uc2  What becomes important is how quickly development planners can recognize these problems and understand whether they constitute a case of a bad choice of technology application or whether they are endemic problems that can be correct in the long run. \par \par \uc2  The writer is a Master of Arts candidate in international relations at the Maxwell School of Citizenship and \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs at Syracuse University, United States. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtc1002nu\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Artha Graha postpones initial offering. \b0\par\par\uc2 470 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 December 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Bank Artha Graha has postponed its plan to sell stocks on the Jakarta Stock Exchange(JSX) following weak market sentiment following the recent monetary crisis, said its Managing Director. \par \par \uc2  The Managing Director of Bank Artha Graha, Anton B. S. Hudyana, said that his company had actually already made all the preparations to come onto the exchange last November. However, he explained, in light of the weak market sentiment, it seemed better to wait until the market is stimulated once again. \par \par \uc2  "Our practical preparations to go \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  have been completed with the underwriting of the emission by PT Danareksa and Trimegah," he said to Bisnis yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Although there has been a monetary fluctuation, according to Anton, his company in the first nine months of this year reaped profits of Rp 11 billion, with a year-end target of Rp 12 billion. "We are optimistic this target will be exceeded." \par \par \uc2  In order to shore up its capital, he said, the Bank Artha Graha stockholders had added Rp 15 billion to the reserve capital last August. Now, he says, the reserve capital is Rp 105 billion and with un-distributed profits will reach Rp 145 billion. \par \par \uc2  With the addition of the capital, according to Anton, the capital adequacy ratio(CAR) of the bank is now 11% and the funds to credit ratio(LDR) is 90-95%. \par \par \uc2  The bank, which is partially owned by Yayasan Eka Paksi, has assets of Rp 1.4 trillion, with outstanding credits of Rp 1.2 trillion. "Despite the monetary crisis, the position of third party funds has been stable at about Rp 1.2 trillion," said Anton. \par \par \uc2  At this time Bank Artha Graha is offering a CD rate of about 26-29%, a reduction from monetary crisis rates, which were 29-33%. In order to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  further this year, he said, must be done very cautiously in mind of the approaching holidays, Christmas, New Year's and Ramadan. \par \par \uc2  "December this year will be different from December last year because the demand for funds will be higher. Further study will be required to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Anton added that his company did not plan a large scale expansion next year, in light of the still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. "Expansion will have to be undertaken very cautiously." \par \par \uc2  He said the recent monetary crisis could lower the quality of their credit portfolio. In order to reduce the negative effects to the banking sector, he hopes the government will be able to provide legal support. "At least, there should be a guarantee of accelerated settlements through the courts." \par \par \uc2  Accelerated settlement through the courts, he said, would at least lighten the burden on the banks resulting from bad debt. "Until now the legal process has always occurred very slowly." (ep). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtc20009a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
