\par\par \b \uc2  Stock prices, rupiah continue to weaken. \b0\par\par\uc2 420 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 December 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) closed marginally lower yesterday on increasing concern about a further decline in the rupiah against the American dollar. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite index closed 4.33 points down at 394.28 as the rupiah broke through the psychological level of 3,800. \par \par \uc2  Head of research of Pentasena Securities Mohammad Syahrial said that the persistent decline in stock prices was caused by a combination of higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the persistent fall of the rupiah against the American dollar, and the bleak outlook of corporate earnings this year and next year. \par \par \uc2  "Political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the face of the upcoming General Assembly meeting to elect new president and vice president in March add to the negative sentiment in the market," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said most foreign investors, who previously accounted for about 70 percent of transactions in the JSX, had long stayed out of the market and would possibly reenter it again in the second semester of 1998. \par \par \uc2  "I think most foreign investors will possibly reenter the market at the earliest in the second semester next year," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that the monetary crisis would affect corporate earnings in 1998. \par \par \uc2  "According to our assessment, most companies will record an average 5 percent decline in net profit next year compared to their earning performance in 1996," he said, adding that corporate earning in 1996 was good. \par \par \uc2  "Most foreign investors have left the market and switched to investing in Asian bonds," he said. \par \par \uc2  Stock analysts said poor earnings expectations due to foreign exchange losses and fears of a prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown continued to batter the stock market sentiment. \par \par \uc2  As stock prices lost ground, the rupiah remained weak against the U.S. dollar yesterday on a contagion effect of the weakening of regional currencies. \par \par \uc2  "The sharp fall in the (South Korean) won has certainly affected other currencies including the rupiah," a dealer from a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign exchange dealers said the rupiah fell to a day low of 3,840 against the greenback yesterday before settling at 3,815/35 at close. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers also attributed the rupiah's fall to rising demand for the greenback from local companies. \par \par \uc2  "Though trading was relatively quiet there is a strong need for local companies to buy dollars to cover their dollar denominated debts which are to mature this month," a dealer said. \par \par \uc2  This force, he said, prompted the rupiah to weaken against the dollar. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtc3002si\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Exchange predicted recovered by second quarter of 1998. \b0\par\par\uc2 510 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 December 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Indonesian capital market is predicted to show improvement only by the second semester of next year, while the Jakarta Stock Exchange(JSX) Composite Price Index will reach a level of 500-600 by the end of next year, said a capital market practitioner. \par \par \uc2  Dandossi Matram, Vice President of PT Bakrie Finance Corp. Tbk., said that the slow recovery of the Indonesian capital market in 1998 would be caused by a number of negative factors, though there are still some positive factors that could advance the development of the exchange. \par \par \uc2  "A number of negative factors exist, including still high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , decreased company performance compared to 1997 and the still high level of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said at a seminar entitled "Implications of the Rupiah Depreciation on \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 " sponsored by the Political Science Department at University of Indonesia and the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce yesterday. \par \par \uc2  On the other hand, there are a number of positive factors, including decreasing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  now approaching normal levels, a normally busy market in the first quarter, the already sharply corrected Jakarta Stock Exchange(JSX)Composite Price Index and Composite Price Index conditions which reflect future \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects. \par \par \uc2  "The conclusion is that the capital market will begin to show recovery in the first or second quarter of 1998, while the Composite Price Index is predicted to be at 500 to 600 by the end of 1998," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to Dandossi, the fundamental conditions also support market development this year and next year. These fundamental conditions include the rate of inflation and the slowly decreasing but still high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which will result in a moderate capital market recovery. "The lending rates at the end of 1997 of 25-35% will be down to 20-30% by the end of 1998." \par \par \uc2  He recommends investment the stock-oriented mutual funds with low net asset value, and long term bonds issues with coupon rated fixed, as the two prospective sectors for 1998. \par \par \uc2  Political will \par \par \uc2  At the same time, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  observer Sjahrir said that improvement in the performance of the capital market at this time will depend highly on the political will of the government, which must be indicated through its policies. \par \par \uc2  Regarding the president's statement in Africa that 1% of all government owned company profits be invested in the capital market, Sajahrir said that this was a positive indication of the government's commitment to the capital market. \par \par \uc2  "The trouble is, if this is not demonstrated through \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , there will be trouble," he said in a press conference related to a seminar entitled 'Mutual Funds Today and in the Future' organized by the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Financial research(ECFIN) yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to Sjahrir, in order to realize the channeling of 200 government owned companies' funds to the capital market, a coordinating body will have to be formed. It will not be easy, but such a body will be highly necessary to contact the tactical departments beforehand and so forth. (06/ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtc5000a6\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Rp tumble no obstacle to debt roll-over'. \b0\par\par\uc2 751 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 December 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Big business is not concerned that the lack of stability in the rupiah will pose an obstacle to the roll-over of its foreign debt. To the contrary, the exchange rate should stabilize immediately with the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce, or Kadin and Indonesian government cooperation. \par \par \uc2  The General Head of KADIN, Aburizal 'Ical Bakrie aid the weakening in the rupiah to Rp 4,000 per US dollar would not impede efforts to obtain rollovers of foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  "I don't think so. It is a normal occurrence and it makes people get used to these conditions," said Ical following a Kadin meeting with Finance Minister, Mar'ie Muhammad, here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Gemala Group Chief, Sofjan Wanandi, also said that the weak rupiah was only a temporary thing and would not go on for long. He was confident the rupiah would not hit Rp 5,000 per US dollar. \par \par \uc2  With the new agreement between the government and Kadin to overcome the monetary crisis together, he said, the rupiah exchange rate will strengthen again since it will bring increased foreign confidence in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "One thing is clear, we will find many ways of resorting this foreign confidence," he said. \par \par \uc2  Previously Sofyan said that he hoped that exporters who are still in possession of dollars form their transactions would not participate in the speculation by holding onto the foreign currency. \par \par \uc2  By releasing their dollars onto the market, said the Gemala Group head, the exporters would help to improve liquidity needed at this tie by the business community to operat4e its businesses. \par \par \uc2  "The improvement of liquidity is on priority for the normalization of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to lower unemployment since at this time many companies have halted operations due to scarcity of funds," he said as quoted by Anatara News Service on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  He stressed that the private sector had an obligation to pay its foreign debt, and the governmetn need not serve as intermediary. \par \par \uc2  Sofyan in fact said that he did not know the governments intent in announcing its \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to stop intervening on the money market. Because, he said, the announcement in fact encouraged people to speculate even more. \par \par \uc2  "As soon as Mar'ie announced that the government would no longer intervene in the money market, speculators began holding onto and in fact searching for dollars, which resulted in further weakening in the rupiah exchange rate against the US dollar." \par \par \uc2  The statements by the governmetn in the last few days, he said, have also resulted in the appearance of an element of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  among the foreign private sector regarding the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and private sector. \par \par \uc2  That is why, said Sofyan, "what we need today is solidarity between the government and the business community in order to restore the confidence of the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  domestically and internationally by bringing an end to the current monetary crisis." \par \par \uc2  Not surprised \par \par \uc2  H. M. Aksa Mahmud, President of the Board of Directors at Bosowa Group said the fall in the rupiah, touching Rp 4,000 had become a normal occurrence, and did not surprise the magnate. \par \par \uc2  Ical added that the rupiah exchange rate would return to normal in the very near future. With the new partnership between the government and the business community targeted at increasing dollar liquidity. \par \par \uc2  Clearly, he said, the current conditions were the responsibility of all sides[government and private]. \par \par \uc2  According to Ical the weakening in the rupiah was caused by continuous strengthening in dollar values against other currencies. For example, the Malay ringgit is at RM 3.8/US$, the Thai baht is at 41 and even the yen is now at 130/US$, from a previous 80/US$, which is a 60% depreciation. "all currencies are weakening against the dollar." \par \par \uc2  Ical said the IMF package could not fight this market trend. "But the IMF package has improved foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , improved \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms and so forth. This is very positive and is not simply related to the dollar fluctuations." \par \par \uc2  Kadin, he said is not simply appealing for the dollar to be used simply for intervention, but to be followed up by BI not selling the dollars onto the market, but directly to the exporters. \par \par \uc2  "This suggestion has yet to be agreed to. But I think the governmetn will want to increase the liquidity to the market, as to whether the SBPU(Money Market Securities) which are now at,.5% should be increased to 10% is now being studied," he said. (m2/ib/ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010929dtc6000ah\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
