\par\par \b \uc2  Legal status of closed bank owners questioned. \b0\par\par\uc2 613 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 December 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , must clarify the legal status of the owners of the 16 banks recently closed by the government, legal experts said here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Economics law consultant Abdul Hakim G. Nusantara said legal aspects regarding the closure of the 16 private banks last month remained unclear, including the legal status of their shareholders. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was reflected in the case of President Soeharto's son Bambang Trihatmodjo, who owned a 25 percent stake in the closed Bank Andromeda, Hakim said. \par \par \uc2  After Bank Andromeda's closure, Bambang, chairman of the Bimantara Group, reportedly acquired the license of Bank Alfa. Bank Alfa's assets and liabilities had earlier been taken over by Bank Risjad Salim International of the giant Salim Group. \par \par \uc2  Bank Alfa has since acquired the assets and liabilities of the closed Bank Andromeda. \par \par \uc2  Hakim said the owners of the closed banks, including those of Bank Andromeda, could be blacklisted by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  if found liable for the mismanagement of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds. \par \par \uc2  However, the implementation of the law did not indicate this, he said at a discussion on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  legal system in the country. \par \par \uc2  "The acquisition of Bank Andromeda (by Bank Alfa) came before Bank Andromeda's liquidation process even began," he said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor J. Soedradjad Djiwandono said in a House of Representative hearing recently that commissioners or owners of the closed banks would not be blacklisted if they were found not responsible for making their banks insolvent. \par \par \uc2  Hakim said it was not clear if the law was imposed on the banks as institutions or the owners themselves. \par \par \uc2  "The criteria for the blacklisting process was not transparent," he said. \par \par \uc2  In the case of Bambang, Hakim said, his motivation for acquiring Bank Alfa could be to speed up Bank Andromeda's liquidation process. \par \par \uc2  "If this could solve the problem of returning funds to depositors, then make it a model solution for the other 15 banks too," Hakim said. \par \par \uc2  Economics legal analyst Hamid Awaludin said yesterday owners of banks which violated the law, could also be prosecuted under criminal charges in addition to administrative sanctions. \par \par \uc2  Hamid said the personal assets of the banks' owners could be liquidated to pay their depositors. \par \par \uc2  However, during the interim between the banks' closures and the time liquidation teams were required to be set up, the finance ministry and \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had not taken any action, he said. \par \par \uc2  "This could encourage the banks' owners to conceal their personal wealth," he said. \par \par \uc2  Abdul Hakim said the government must also address issues on bank transparency before it could regain \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  trust, he said. \par \par \uc2  Hakim said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  must also review its concept of bank secrecy, since it had been used as a shield to cover financial problems. \par \par \uc2  "Bank secrecy is supposed to protect depositors, so that the banks cannot disclose any information regarding their depositors," said Pradjoto, a legal consultant of Pradjoto and Partners. \par \par \uc2  Former House of Representative member Tadjudin Noer Said stated at yesterday's discussion that the government tended to reform the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  only when it faced hardship. \par \par \uc2  He said \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms seemed to be established in reaction to urgent needs, instead of being carefully planned. \par \par \uc2  "It seems we only deregulate or cut bureaucratic tape when we need to borrow money," Tadjudin, known as an outspoken house member representing the ruling Golkar during the 1992-1997 period, said. \par \par \uc2  As a result, many legal aspects of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms remained unclear, he said. \par \par \uc2  When Singapore was reforming its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it focussed its attention on the legal aspects, he said. \par \par \uc2  In Indonesia, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform to be less effective, he said. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtc90032c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
