\par\par \b \uc2  Try Sutrisno appeases confusion over politics. \b0\par\par\uc2 565 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 December 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Vice President Try Sutrisno has called on Indonesian people, especially youth, not to be confused about the current political situation. \par \par \uc2  The vice president urged young people not to be influenced by certain groups' attempts to disturb national unity and integrity. \par \par \uc2  He did not identify the groups or the political situation which he deemed a cause for concern. However, the country has over the past year been beset by various social, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political woes. \par \par \uc2  The latest situation has been \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by circulating rumors about President Soeharto's ailing health, which has also adversely affected the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Bapak (Try) has made us aware that in understanding the ongoing political situation, especially in connection with the People's Consultative Assembly in March, we must stick to the Constitution," chairman of the Ansor Youth Movement, M. Iqbal Assegaf, said after his meeting with Try at Merdeka Palace yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Ansor is affiliated with the Nahdlatul Ulama (NU). NU claims itself as one of the country's largest Moslem organizations with at least 30 million members. \par \par \uc2  Accompanied by five other Ansor executives, Iqbal reported to Try on the latest developments of the organization. \par \par \uc2  The People's Consultative Assembly will convene in March to elect a new president and vice president and endorse the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Guidelines. \par \par \uc2  President Soeharto, 76, is widely expected to be reelected for a seventh consecutive term in March. He has been silent about whether or not he will accept his renomination. \par \par \uc2  Given Soeharto's age, the vice presidential position is regarded as even more important for the nation's future. \par \par \uc2  According to the 1945 Constitution, the vice president is supposed to take over the presidential post if the president cannot perform his duties. \par \par \uc2  "Our duty is to be consistent in following the Constitution and system which we have agreed upon," Try told Ansor leaders. \par \par \uc2  Try is the fifth deputy under Soeharto since the President became the head of state in 1967. \par \par \uc2  Try's predecessors are the late Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono IX (a civilian), the late Adam Malik (a civilian), Umar Wirahadikusumah (a retired Army general), and Sudharmono (a retired Army general). All of them served only one term. \par \par \uc2  Soeharto had actually wanted Sultan to be his vice president from 1978 to 1983. However, Sultan turned down the offer citing his poor health. \par \par \uc2  Try, 62, is a retired Army general and was former Armed Forces (ABRI) commander from 1988 to 1993 before taking the position as the country's second most powerful leader in March 1993. \par \par \uc2  Try served as Soeharto's adjutant from 1974 to 1978. Palace officials recalled him as being one of Soeharto's favorite adjutants. \par \par \uc2  "Pak Try has a good sense of humor and Pak Harto was often entertained by his fresh jokes," one palace official recalled. \par \par \uc2  Soeharto's six children were still young when Try worked as his aide. His eldest daughter Siti Hardiyanti Rukmana was 25 years old at the time, and his youngest son, Hutomo, was about 13 years old. \par \par \uc2  "At that time, they referred to Try as Mas (older brother)," said the officials. \par \par \uc2  Besides Try, several other figures have been tipped to become the next vice president, including State Minister of Research and Technology B.J. Habibie, State Minister of National Development Planning Ginandjar Kartasasmita, Minister of Information R. Hartono and Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono. (prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtch003bc\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
