\par\par \b \uc2  Special team needed to settle crisis - Bambang. \b0\par\par\uc2 455 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 December 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Leading businessman Bambang Trihatmodjo called yesterday for the establishment of a special team of professionals to help the government tackle the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Bambang, who is President Soeharto's second son, told reporters on the sidelines of a People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) meeting yesterday that such a team was needed to follow up on the President's general \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. \par \par \uc2  He also called on his father to include players from the private sector along with government officials. "I really hope Pak Harto will set up a special team to handle the crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  Egged on by reporters, he confirmed that the reason for the team was the current cabinet ministers' reportedly slow response and poor initiative in handling the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "That's the reason why I suggested the establishment of the special team," said Bambang, who was also hit by the crisis when a bank he partially owned, Bank Andromeda, was closed down by the government on Nov. 1. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil took a turn for the worse last week and earlier this week when rumors spread that President Soeharto had died and that a coup attempt was brewing. \par \par \uc2  After weeks of taking a batter, the rupiah rallied yesterday and increased against the U.S. dollar following President Soeharto's first \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  appearance after a 10-day rest. The President led the graduation of the Indonesian military academy at the palace compound. \par \par \uc2  "I expect this (appearance) will help restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  trust in the government and its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies," Bambang said. "It should also end all rumors about my father's health." \par \par \uc2  Analysts have called on the government to restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence in the market, its policies and the currency. \par \par \uc2  Businessman Sofjan Wanandi said recently that one way to restore confidence was to end \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Indonesia's future leadership. He said dominant Golkar should immediately announce its vice presidential candidate. \par \par \uc2  But Bambang, who is also a Golkar legislator at the MPR, said this was not necessary. \par \par \uc2  "We already have the mechanism that vice presidential candidates will be announced in the MPR general assembly next March," he said. "There's not long to wait, only about two and a half months." \par \par \uc2  Golkar chairman Harmoko and senior member Akbar Tanjung also dismissed the possibility of announcing the vice presidential candidate now. \par \par \uc2  "We have to uphold our political system. Constitutionally, the vice presidential candidate will be announced in an MPR general assembly," Harmoko said. "Golkar will consult its vice presidential candidate with the elected president next March." \par \par \uc2  Harmoko said there was no guarantee that announcing the vice presidential candidate ahead of the schedule would help stabilize the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (imn) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dtcj003dj\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Monetary Council needs extended authority. \b0\par\par\uc2 924 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 December 1997\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Monetary Council should be given full authority to implement an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stabilization program, with the support of concrete action by the team of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers, in order to restore confidence in the rupiah, said an economist. \par \par \uc2  "The work of the existing ministerial team needs to be optimized. The monetary council needs to be given full authority to take action to stabilize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Professor Anwar Nasution, on the University of Indonesia Economics faculty, to Bisnis Indonesia during a conference called 'Sustaining \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Growth in Indonesia' in Jakarta yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to Anwar, the government does not need to form a special team to restore the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as Thailand and Malaysia have done. \par \par \uc2  The existing government team[the monetary council] can be used if it is given the authority. At this time they are not being given that authority," said Anwar. \par \par \uc2  The Monetary Council is headed by the Finance Minister, and peopled by the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor and ministers in the financial and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fields. At this time the Monetary Council is headed by Mar'ie Muhammad and peopled by the BI Governor J. Soedradjad Djiwandono, Secretary of State Moerdiono and a number of economics related ministers. \par \par \uc2  Director of Presetya Mulya School of Management, Djisman S. Simanjuntak, said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers need to take action together to bring an end to the monetary crisis because the business community is losing confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation and the rupiah exchange rate. \par \par \uc2  "What can restore that confidence is government action. There is no such action at this time because all of it depends on the president." \par \par \uc2  Senior economist, M. Sadli, also had comment. He said the key to the settlement of the crisis at this time is with President Soeharto. "The key only lies with President Soeharto," he said at Brawijaya University, Malang, yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He said that it is difficult to predict how long the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis will go on. All of it, he said, leads back to President Soeharto. But he did not say what the president should do about it. \par \par \uc2  Remove \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  At a separate location, money market practitioner Theo F. Toemion said the monetary authority will have to go all out to oppose speculators on the money market, using the year-end as the right time to intervene to stabilize the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  At this time, he said, rupiah liquidity at the banks, which has the potential to be converted to US dollars, is about Rp 11 trillion, while the foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  owned by the Bank of Indonesia is US$ 21 billion. \par \par \uc2  "If these \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  are multiplied at an exchange rate of Rp 5,000, then the total would be Rp 115 trillion. With this amount to use, I am convinced the monetary authority would have the strength to oppose the speculators." \par \par \uc2  Now, he said, is the right time for BI to intervene because the market is in the process of closing its books, there is no interbank market operating and trade is slow. \par \par \uc2  According to Theo, if BI is bold enough to make a large intervention on the money market at this time it will be effective in restoring the strength of the rupiah to the Rp 3,500 level by year end, though there is a potential for renewed weakening at year end. \par \par \uc2  However, such an intervention would not be sufficient, and it must be accompanied by a government commitment to consistently guard the fundamental factors. "We cannot be immediately satisfied with bringing the rupiah to that level[Rp 3,500]." \par \par \uc2  Sadli said that BI must also increase its oversight and be more transparent regarding the banking community. Weak oversight and low transparency by BI, he said, were on e trigger of the fall in the rupiah exchange value. \par \par \uc2  "The very high number of private banks and the lack of transparency in the allocation of bank funds have made the depositors begin to lose confidence in the banks," he said. \par \par \uc2  Announce policies \par \par \uc2  Sri Mulyani Indrawati, an economist at UI, added that the government should immediately implement a credible \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in order to convince investors that Indonesia is safe. \par \par \uc2  Without such action, she said, everyone will be waiting for stabilization to until March 1998, which means six months will have been lost needlessly to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  And yet, said Sri, there is already more than sufficient \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The difficulty is that the policies are not working because "political negotiations have not been settled" in their implementation. \par \par \uc2  If we are forced to wait for the formation of a new cabinet and new cabinet leaders, then socio-political expectations are likely to arise. "Because the virus has spread everywhere." \par \par \uc2  Djisman said the election of the president following the general assembly of the People's Consultative Council(which is elected by the populace, and which actually elects the government officials, such as the president, in its five-yearly session in March) will at least have an announcement affect which will bring strengthening to the rupiah. "But this must also be accompanied by the selection of a cabinet which is trusted by the market." \par \par \uc2  Regarding other short term solutions, Djisman also said that there is a need to 